This is an introductory course that gives an overview of the development of semiotics into an academic discipline with its basic issues and directions of study. Topics: semiosis and its components; dimensions of semiosis (syntactics, semanitics, pragmatics); generating and interpretating signs. Semiotics will be introduced in relations with other humanities.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing an overview of the historical development of and main topics in semiotics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course  1. has the knowledge of the basic concepts and appraoches of semiotics; 4. has acquired the foundations for independent semiotic thinking.
